(thirdQuint)Assessment of the WATCHMAN Device in Patients Unsuitable for Oral Anticoagulation.

 The ASAP-TOO study is a prospective, randomized, multi-center, global investigation to establish the safety and effectiveness of the WATCHMAN Device for subjects with non-valvular atrial fibrillation who are deemed not suitable for anti-coagulation therapy to reduce the risk of stroke.

 Subjects will be randomized in a ratio of 2 Device to 1 Control to receive the WATCHMAN LAA closure device (Device) or the control treatment of single antiplatelet medication or no medication at the discretion of the study physician (Control).

 All randomized subjects will follow the protocol required tests and assessments at each scheduled follow-up visit.

